# Ex1 Anti-Patterns

See `docs/ex1-mistakes.md`. Ex1 grade 76 — algorithm OK, C++ hygiene and runtime need work.

## Never repeat

| Pattern | Code |
|---------|------|
| `namespace su = mp_units::...` inside functions | e17s |
| `ScanProbing`, `ScanOptions`, `TickSnapshot` with raw doubles | e16n |
| `ErrorLogger::lines()` exposing internal vector | e22m |
| `SimulationState::setTruthCell` — unneeded public API | e08m |
| Non-const `scan()` when read-only | e07m |
| Slow runs on small maps | b05s |
| Missing file → no error handling | b06m |
| Deferred error flush at end of run (`flushIfNeeded`) | ex2 violation — log immediately per run |

## Do not port

`ScanProbing`, `TickSnapshot`, `SimulationState`, ex1 `ErrorLogger` (deferred flush or `lines()`), ex1 `main` loop (whole-program abort), txt parsers.

## Safe to reuse ideas

Frontier/BFS → `MappingAlgorithmImpl::nextStep`; collision checks → `MockMovement`; scoring math → `MapsComparison`.
